<link rel="shortcut icon" href="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/all/themes/bfi2013/favicon.ico" type="image/vnd.microsoft.icon" />
<meta name="description" content="André Bazin, the high priest of realism, practically invented film studies. It&amp;#039;s time he was rehabilitated from postmodern sneers, argues Peter Matthews. This piece from 1999 is republished in honour of Bazin&amp;#039;s centenary." />
